  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sector response to heightened food insecurity in North-eastern Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving nutrition; health; and water, sanitation and hygiene assistance to internally displaced people and host community members in northeast Nigeria. This UNICEF project provides preventative and curative nutrition services for children and women; supports the local authorities to provide primary healthcare and antenatal services; improves health referral services in IDP caps and host communities; rehabilitates water and sanitation facilities; and promotes hygiene services. The nutrition component of the project provides life-saving assistance to 112,000 people, including 95,000 women, 5,000 men, 12,000 children, and 3,360 persons with disabilities. The health component provides life-saving assistance to 500,000 people, including 208,000 women, 192,000 men, 100,000 children and 15,000 persons with disabilities. The water, sanitation and hygiene component provides life-saving assistance to 150,000 people, including 36,000 women, 31,000 men, 83,000 children and 4,500 persons living with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
